WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:03.742
Hey, Jake,
I'm back from the framers.

00:03.786 --> 00:07.224
I can't wait to get
this thing hung up on the wall.

00:07.268 --> 00:11.098
Well, you won't have
to wait long, little lady.

00:11.141 --> 00:16.016
There's a new sheriff in town,
and that frame is about to hang.

00:17.017 --> 00:20.063
Mm. Ah, ah, ah.[whirring]

00:20.107 --> 00:21.543
[exhales sharply]

00:21.586 --> 00:23.197
[Southern accent]: Are you sure
that you're the sheriff?

00:23.240 --> 00:25.808
Can I see your badge?

00:25.851 --> 00:27.592
Well, you're gonna have
to wait about five minutes.

00:27.636 --> 00:29.420
I was just upstairs
polishing it.

00:29.464 --> 00:32.771
Okay, guys, hi. Hi, guys. Um...

00:32.815 --> 00:34.773
Before you get too deep
into your cowboy role-play,

00:34.817 --> 00:37.037
I just wanted to let you know
I'm in the room.JAKE: Oh, no, it's...

00:37.080 --> 00:38.864
You can stay, Cooper.

00:38.908 --> 00:42.172
Well, I guess I do
live here rent-free.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.435
Give me one second, I'll go
upstairs, get my cowboy hat.

00:44.479 --> 00:46.785
No, no, no, no. No.What? What? No. No. No.

00:46.829 --> 00:49.701
Ha-ha. He means we're actually
hanging a photo. See?What? Oh.

00:49.745 --> 00:50.789
It's from our wedding.

00:50.833 --> 00:51.790
Aw.
Yeah.

00:51.834 --> 00:53.357
You were so emotional.

00:53.401 --> 00:54.837
And, Claire, you look gorgeous.

00:56.665 --> 00:58.667
Step aside, Jake.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.756
Your mother-in-law is here
to teach you how to screw.

01:02.105 --> 01:04.455
Say something, Gerald.
I made it weird.

01:04.499 --> 01:05.717
GERALD:
Uh...

01:05.761 --> 01:09.156
Make way. Daddy's big drill
is coming through.

01:10.809 --> 01:13.247
I made it worse.

01:15.597 --> 01:16.772
Uh, Claire,
what are your parents

01:16.815 --> 01:18.426
doing in our house again?

01:18.469 --> 01:21.168
Oh. I-I just mentioned to them
that we were hanging a picture,

01:21.211 --> 01:22.560
and they came over to help.

01:22.604 --> 01:24.780
But I spent my whole morning
learning how to do this.

01:24.823 --> 01:27.522
I started off googling
"well hung pictures," and...

01:29.132 --> 01:31.917
...let's just say my confidence
could use a boost.

01:31.961 --> 01:33.702
It's all good,
Jake. We got it.

01:33.745 --> 01:35.878
Already got my
stud finder out.

01:35.921 --> 01:37.619
Beep. Beep, beep,
beep. Uh-oh.

01:37.662 --> 01:39.055
It looks like he found one.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.622
Beep, beep, beep,
beep, beep, beep.

01:40.665 --> 01:42.493
Beep, beep, beep-- wow!

01:42.537 --> 01:44.278
[laughs]

01:44.321 --> 01:45.453
Ha, ha.

01:45.496 --> 01:47.281
Picture hung.
[whoops]

01:47.324 --> 01:49.152
Construction work is hard.
Feels like we earned ourselves

01:49.196 --> 01:50.284
a couple cold ones.

01:50.327 --> 01:52.764
Already got 'em chilling
in my purse, baby.

01:52.808 --> 01:54.984
[laughs]:
Yeah.[laughs]

01:55.027 --> 01:56.855
Bye.Bye. Thank you.

01:56.899 --> 01:58.944
Bye.
Mm.
Bye.

01:58.988 --> 02:00.511
Man, I love
living with you guys.

02:00.555 --> 02:02.600
It's so nice to be
with a family of young adults

02:02.644 --> 02:04.472
who aren't too proud
to let the older generation

02:04.515 --> 02:07.039
do everything for 'em.

02:09.738 --> 02:11.392
Claire, did you hear that?

02:11.435 --> 02:13.698
Yeah. He called us young.

02:13.742 --> 02:18.050
No, I'm talking about your
parents doing everything for us.

02:18.094 --> 02:20.183
Cooper's right. I mean,
look at our wedding photo.

02:20.227 --> 02:23.708
They chose the venue,
the flowers, your mom deejayed.

02:25.145 --> 02:27.190
The only thing
I got to choose was you.

02:27.234 --> 02:29.714
Aw.
Mm-mm, Claire,

02:29.758 --> 02:32.891
don't get lost in my buttery
sweetness. I'm upset.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.893
Come on, you know
how my parents are.

02:34.937 --> 02:37.853
They love to do stuff for me
'cause I'm their pride and joy.

02:37.896 --> 02:40.899
Also, they're afraid that
I'm gonna put them in a home.

02:44.338 --> 02:45.774
Well, now that they're
retired, it's like

02:45.817 --> 02:47.558
they took all their energy
from being doctors

02:47.602 --> 02:49.517
and focused it entirely on us.

02:49.560 --> 02:51.301
Well, us and drinking.

02:52.955 --> 02:55.566
Well, us and drinking
and denying climate change.

02:57.742 --> 03:01.137
♪ Imagine me and you, I do

03:01.181 --> 03:04.053
♪ I think about you
day and night ♪

03:04.096 --> 03:05.663
♪ It's only right

03:05.707 --> 03:08.449
♪ So happy together.

03:08.492 --> 03:10.755
[vocalizing]

03:20.287 --> 03:21.244
[coughing]

03:21.288 --> 03:22.245
[sniffles]

03:22.289 --> 03:24.639
Hey.

03:24.682 --> 03:27.381
As soon as I got your text
about being sick,

03:27.424 --> 03:30.558
I went straight to CVS to pick
up a little Claire-package.

03:30.601 --> 03:34.823
Uh, we've got DayQuil,
uh, VapoRub,

03:34.866 --> 03:36.607
and both Imodium and Ex-Lax,

03:36.651 --> 03:39.480
depending on the direction
of traffic.

03:39.523 --> 03:42.004
Thanks. Uh, but what about work?

03:42.047 --> 03:43.832
Ah, they're having a diversity
seminar, and I want them all

03:43.875 --> 03:45.877
to sweat when they see
I'm not there.

03:48.315 --> 03:49.794
I'm just so happy
you called me first,

03:49.838 --> 03:52.841
and not your parents...That'll be all, Nurse Davis.

03:52.884 --> 03:54.625
Mom and Dad are scrubbing in.

03:54.669 --> 03:57.846
What are they doing here?

03:57.889 --> 03:59.717
I swear, I didn't call them.

03:59.761 --> 04:03.286
They came by to fix the garden
hose so they could wash my car,

04:03.330 --> 04:04.679
and then, I don't know,

04:04.722 --> 04:08.509
they just, they just
heard me sneezing.

04:08.552 --> 04:10.859
This is exactly
what I'm talking about.

04:10.902 --> 04:12.513
No, this is different,
because I am sick,

04:12.556 --> 04:14.341
and they're doctors.

04:14.384 --> 04:19.302
And plus, I don't like you
seeing me when I'm all gross.

04:19.346 --> 04:22.566
Claire-bear, two months
into dating, you got so wasted

04:22.610 --> 04:25.961
at a frat party,
you threw up a whole hot dog.

04:27.397 --> 04:29.573
Sure, I had questions,

04:29.617 --> 04:32.533
but I still thought you were
the hottest girl in the world.

04:32.576 --> 04:37.277
Man, if I had kept it down,
I would've won that contest.

04:39.714 --> 04:43.805
My point is, eventually,
we're gonna have kids, right?

04:43.848 --> 04:46.938
And when we do, I want
to be the one you rely on.

04:46.982 --> 04:48.766
Please let me prove
I can take care of you.

04:48.810 --> 04:51.247
Aw. Well, that's really sweet.
[chuckles]

04:51.291 --> 04:55.556
Okay. Uh, hey, uh, Mom, Dad?
You guys can go.

04:55.599 --> 04:56.948
Uh, Jake's gonna
take care of me.

04:56.992 --> 04:59.255
[both laughing]

05:08.873 --> 05:12.312
Oh, my gosh. She's serious.

05:12.355 --> 05:14.662
Jake, I-I don't want
to question your manhood

05:14.705 --> 05:16.707
in front of your wife, so...Thank you.

05:16.751 --> 05:18.666
...can we do this
in the kitchen instead?

05:20.189 --> 05:22.147
[sighs]

05:22.191 --> 05:23.714
All right, look,
I know you guys are nervous,

05:23.758 --> 05:26.151
but I've taken care of Claire
when she's sick. All right?

05:26.195 --> 05:28.458
Okay. Just so you know,
when Claire is sick,

05:28.502 --> 05:30.112
she needs a ton of blankets...

05:30.155 --> 05:32.375
Blankets. Yeah, yeah.
I got her covered.On-- okay. Oh.

05:32.419 --> 05:35.030
Oh, okay. Well, she also needs
a steady rotation of herYeah.

05:35.073 --> 05:36.771
favorite movies. Mm-hmm.Favorite movies. Yes, I got it.

