05:51.394 --> 05:55.398
Ni hao.

05:59.576 --> 06:02.492
Well, as a wise village elder
once said to me...

06:02.536 --> 06:04.364
[clears throat]

06:04.407 --> 06:06.061
...get the hell out of my house.

06:13.938 --> 06:17.551
All right,
my little petri dish.

06:17.594 --> 06:20.249
I got a hot towel to help
open up your sinuses.

06:20.292 --> 06:24.601
Here you go, my little
baby boo-- ew!

06:24.645 --> 06:26.081
Oh, man.

06:26.124 --> 06:27.604
Ugh.

06:27.648 --> 06:30.172
Why are you just
staring at the ceiling?

06:30.215 --> 06:33.262
'Cause you look like E.T.
when he started getting ashy.

06:37.527 --> 06:40.617
But I love you, and I'm gonna
help you get through this.

06:40.661 --> 06:44.229
So here's a towel for your face.
Wear it as long as you'd like.

06:47.711 --> 06:49.234
Ooh. Thanks, baby.

06:49.278 --> 06:50.540
You're welcome.

06:50.584 --> 06:52.934
[sneezes]
Aw...

06:52.977 --> 06:54.979
That was kind of cute.

06:55.023 --> 06:56.285
A little dab for you.
[chuckles]

06:56.328 --> 06:57.982
[sneezes][shouts]

06:58.026 --> 07:00.855
Come on!

07:00.898 --> 07:02.422
Ugh.

07:03.727 --> 07:04.946
Oh, my God, Jake.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.427
These lettuce wraps
are incredible.

07:07.470 --> 07:09.603
I might write a
song about them.
Really?

07:09.646 --> 07:12.693
Nah. I mostly write songs
about butts.

07:14.172 --> 07:15.347
Claire, can I make you a plate?

07:15.391 --> 07:16.610
Oh, not right now.

07:16.653 --> 07:18.394
This cough medicine's
giving me a nice buzz,

07:18.438 --> 07:20.657
and I don't want
to mess that up.

07:20.701 --> 07:22.354
Well, how about another movie?

07:22.398 --> 07:24.313
Hey, uh, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

07:24.356 --> 07:25.488
What are you guys doing here?

07:25.532 --> 07:27.142
I said I have everything
under control.

07:27.185 --> 07:30.319
You have snot in your eyebrow.

07:32.843 --> 07:35.585
We respected your wishes
as long as we could,

07:35.629 --> 07:37.935
but now we are here to
relieve you of your duties.

07:37.979 --> 07:39.459
That's right.
We appreciate all your efforts

07:39.502 --> 07:40.895
and so on and so forth,

07:40.938 --> 07:43.506
blah, blah, blah.Okay. Dad, stop.

07:43.550 --> 07:45.116
No, Jake is doing a great job.

07:45.160 --> 07:47.510
I see all the blankets
and the movies.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.251
What about
the lettuce wraps?

07:49.294 --> 07:50.513
They're amazing. Try them.

07:54.038 --> 07:54.996
JAKE:
Mm-hmm.

07:55.039 --> 07:56.650
Yeah.Mmm. Wow.

07:56.693 --> 07:58.826
Kid's got moves.

07:58.869 --> 08:00.828
These are actually good.Mm-hmm.

08:00.871 --> 08:04.701
As a wise Jake once said,
you're damn right they're good.

08:06.790 --> 08:10.620
Honey, I-I can't believe
I'm saying this,

08:10.664 --> 08:12.840
but I think Jake has everything
under control.

08:12.883 --> 08:16.496
I know. Gerald, I don't, I don't
think they need us anymore.

08:16.539 --> 08:17.801
JAKE:
Eh, well, guys,

08:17.845 --> 08:19.368
I know it's hard
to let go of your baby, but...

08:19.411 --> 08:21.936
We're free![both laugh]

08:23.067 --> 08:24.025
Wait, what?

08:24.068 --> 08:25.548
Ugh, we have been
living our lives

08:25.592 --> 08:28.420
at half buzz
just in case, but Gerald...

08:30.422 --> 08:32.555
...now that we're off the hook,
we can finally go crazy,

08:32.599 --> 08:34.731
like, North Florida crazy.

08:34.775 --> 08:36.733
[laughs]

08:37.778 --> 08:40.302
Come on, baby, let's go.

08:40.345 --> 08:43.348
Hey, dude. Take this.

08:47.222 --> 08:48.702
Now that we've got them
out of our hair,

08:48.745 --> 08:54.011
it's just me and my beautiful--
why do you look like that?

08:54.055 --> 08:55.752
Goodness.

08:58.799 --> 09:02.367
Hey, guys.
Man, I don't feel good.

09:02.411 --> 09:04.587
Oh, no, I hope you didn't
catch what I have.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.067
No. I think it's food poisoning.

09:06.110 --> 09:08.112
Oh. That's what
those noises were?

09:08.156 --> 09:11.246
I thought you were slowly
deflating a balloon.

09:15.729 --> 09:18.209
Man, I'm sorry, Cooper.

09:18.253 --> 09:20.472
Wait, aren't you performing
at the VMAs tonight?

09:20.516 --> 09:22.910
Yeah. Yeah, I'll just, uh,
I'll just have to power through.

09:22.953 --> 09:24.868
Uh, are you sure
that's a good idea?

09:24.912 --> 09:27.610
Ah, it's just, it's just
an upset stomach. I'll be fine.

09:27.654 --> 09:29.525
I mean, all I'm doing
is flying over the audience

09:29.569 --> 09:31.483
in a white angel costume,
while performing a cover

09:31.527 --> 09:34.095
of "Drop It Like It's Hot."

09:34.138 --> 09:35.966
Okay, uh...

09:36.010 --> 09:39.883
I think, uh,
you got to stay home, buddy.

09:39.927 --> 09:40.884
Is that even an option?
I don't think

09:40.928 --> 09:42.407
I've ever taken a day off work.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.409
Oh, yeah, I guess
for rock stars,

09:44.453 --> 09:46.237
a sick day usually
just means rehab.

09:52.200 --> 09:54.245
Ugh, so what did
you eat today, anyway?

09:54.289 --> 09:56.247
The only thing I've had
are Jake's lettuce wraps.

09:56.291 --> 09:57.597
JAKE:
Okay.

09:57.640 --> 09:58.859
Before we start throwing
accusations around

09:58.902 --> 10:01.731
that we can't take back,
let me just say,

10:01.775 --> 10:04.429
it wasn't the wraps
and you're a filthy liar.

10:04.473 --> 10:06.562
Yeah-- Jake.

10:06.606 --> 10:08.085
[high-pitched]: It wasn't
my wraps. It's not my wraps.

10:10.174 --> 10:12.612
Your parents had them,
and they're fine.

10:12.655 --> 10:14.701
You...

10:16.485 --> 10:20.576
You did this to us
with your lettuce wraps.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.579
They poisoned us in the middle
of our tennis match while...

10:23.623 --> 10:26.974
[moans]
Oh, I'm so sorry, Gerald. No.

10:27.017 --> 10:28.497
No. No.
No.

10:28.540 --> 10:29.846
I'm sorry,
it's happening.

10:31.674 --> 10:33.633
[sniffling, panting]

10:35.678 --> 10:41.292
We tried to make it back
to our house, but we couldn't.

10:41.336 --> 10:44.252
Jake, I need you
to move my car.

10:44.295 --> 10:46.297
It's the one
with the doors open,

10:46.341 --> 10:49.257
still running,
parked in your bushes.

10:58.396 --> 10:59.833
That one's out of order.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.878
[moans]

11:10.365 --> 11:11.540
So, we were just about to beat

11:11.583 --> 11:13.498
our old tennis rivals,
The Richardsons...

11:13.542 --> 11:16.110
Oh, we had those cocky S.O.B.s
right where we wanted them.

11:16.153 --> 11:19.069
Set point.

11:19.113 --> 11:20.723
Okay, Mom, you're not
on the court anymore.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.072
Come sit down.Oh, no.

11:22.116 --> 11:23.857
