we might as well

14:19.641 --> 14:21.425
move our burial plots
to the backyard

14:21.469 --> 14:22.905
because we are
gonna be taking care

14:22.949 --> 14:25.386
of these dummies
for eternity.

14:27.431 --> 14:29.259
[sighs]
You know what? Fine, fine.

14:29.303 --> 14:31.261
Here, look. I'll
eat one. All right?

14:31.305 --> 14:32.610
You want me to eat one,
I'll eat one.

14:32.654 --> 14:33.916
No, Jake, you don't
have to do this.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.048
It's okay if you messed up.

14:35.091 --> 14:37.964
[laughing]:
Claire, I didn't mess up.

14:38.007 --> 14:40.314
[high-pitched]: It's not,
it's not the wraps. It's not.

14:41.619 --> 14:42.620
It's not the wraps, okay?

14:42.664 --> 14:44.100
I can take care
of our family

14:44.144 --> 14:47.538
by myself and I'll prove it.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.500
Mmm.

14:55.329 --> 14:58.245
You got about 20 minutes
to get your affairs in order.

15:02.118 --> 15:05.730
Hey. How's my little
Febreze commercial?

15:05.774 --> 15:07.732
[groaning]

15:07.776 --> 15:11.649
So, my lettuce wraps have had
three hours of tummy time,

15:11.693 --> 15:12.824
and guess what?

15:12.868 --> 15:16.611
[singsongy]:
I feel incredible.

15:16.654 --> 15:19.135
[all groaning]I'm sorry, I, uh,

15:19.179 --> 15:20.441
don't speak groan,

15:20.484 --> 15:22.095
but what I assume
you said was,

15:22.138 --> 15:24.749
"Thank you so much for taking
good care of our daughter."

15:24.793 --> 15:26.751
"Sorry we ever doubted you."

15:26.795 --> 15:31.234
"P.S. That's a
great haircut."

15:31.278 --> 15:32.627
Thank you, Gerald.

15:32.670 --> 15:34.672
Yours, too.

15:37.023 --> 15:39.155
We are sorry, Jake.

15:39.199 --> 15:41.853
You didn't poison us and
you're doing an amazing job.

15:41.897 --> 15:43.594
And...?

15:43.638 --> 15:45.901
It is a nice haircut.

15:45.945 --> 15:48.556
All right. Well, thank you two.

15:48.599 --> 15:49.905
Who wants OJ?

15:51.254 --> 15:52.516
There you go.

15:52.560 --> 15:56.477
[affected]:
We've got some water for Cooper.

15:56.520 --> 15:58.783
[groans]Bonnie, would you...?

15:58.827 --> 16:00.742
Oh, no, no, no.
I-I made my own.

16:00.785 --> 16:04.702
It's a special elixir
from Dr. Smirnoff.

16:04.746 --> 16:09.011
Well, I'm gonna go to the
kitchen where I will continue

16:09.055 --> 16:12.928
to be the most badass
caretaker on the planet.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.147
I love you, babe.

16:14.190 --> 16:15.322
I love you, too, boo.

16:21.458 --> 16:22.894
[panting]:
I'm gonna d...

16:22.938 --> 16:24.940
I'm gonna d...
I'm gonna die.

16:24.984 --> 16:26.159
I'm gonna die.

16:26.202 --> 16:31.033
I'm g... I'm gonna die.

16:31.077 --> 16:32.861
[laughs, coughs]

16:32.904 --> 16:34.341
GERALD: Jake?CLAIRE: Jake?

16:34.384 --> 16:36.560
Jake...Jake, we're really
cold in here.

16:36.604 --> 16:38.649
Come back, Jake.JAKE: Coming!

16:42.436 --> 16:44.568
You can do this, Jake.
Jake, you can do th...

16:44.612 --> 16:47.093
[gags, coughs]

16:47.136 --> 16:49.182
Jake, you can do... [gags]

16:49.225 --> 16:51.445
You can do this, man.

16:54.448 --> 16:56.624
Okay.

16:56.667 --> 17:00.106
Dug up a space heater
from the garage.

17:00.149 --> 17:02.064
And since Claire's
using all the blankets,

17:02.108 --> 17:04.675
I brought in floor mats
from the car to keep you warm.

17:04.719 --> 17:06.460
I'll take the passenger side.

17:06.503 --> 17:10.029
Thanks for everything, Jake.

17:10.072 --> 17:11.943
And remember,
I will be your rock

17:11.987 --> 17:15.556
until you all feel
as good as I do. [groans]

17:15.599 --> 17:18.559
[doorbell rings]

17:18.602 --> 17:20.778
Plugged in the
space heater.

17:20.822 --> 17:21.823
[sighs]

17:22.824 --> 17:25.348
Wayne, hey.
Hello, hi.

17:25.392 --> 17:26.828
Cooper, your manager's here.WAYNE: I came to see

17:26.871 --> 17:29.265
how you all are feeling,
and by "you all," I mean Cooper.

17:29.309 --> 17:30.832
What are all
those things, Wayne?

17:30.875 --> 17:33.008
Well, ever since you
posted that video,

17:33.052 --> 17:35.358
our office has been overrun
with "get well" presents

17:35.402 --> 17:36.707
from your fans.

17:36.751 --> 17:38.492
They even sent a
cantaloupe Cooper.

17:39.884 --> 17:41.060
There was a torso, too,

17:41.103 --> 17:43.801
but I got a little hungry
on the way over.

17:43.845 --> 17:45.847
Wayne, could you close the door?
We're all really cold.

17:45.890 --> 17:49.068
Yeah. Turn up the ole
space heater for you guys.

17:49.111 --> 17:51.461
There.

17:51.505 --> 17:54.116
Hey, uh, Wayne, can I talk
to you in the kitchen?

17:54.160 --> 17:55.552
Oh, sure. Nothing more fun

17:55.596 --> 17:57.685
than a little bro time,
or so I've heard.

18:00.688 --> 18:03.386
Oh.

18:03.430 --> 18:05.562
Wayne, can I
ask you something?

18:05.606 --> 18:08.478
If this is about us having
a boys' night, I am in.

18:08.522 --> 18:11.394
No, I'm the one who gave
everyone food poisoning,

18:11.438 --> 18:13.004
including myself.

18:13.048 --> 18:14.136
I need you to help me make sure

18:14.180 --> 18:15.268
that no one finds out
that I am sick

18:15.311 --> 18:16.617
because I am killing it.

18:16.660 --> 18:19.098
Congratulations.
Your couch is on fire.

18:19.141 --> 18:20.142
Hell yeah, it is.

18:20.186 --> 18:21.404
I know I use
a lot of slang,

18:21.448 --> 18:23.232
but your couch is
literally on fire.

18:23.276 --> 18:24.668
Oh, my God!

18:26.017 --> 18:27.454
I put the space heater
too close.

18:27.497 --> 18:29.499
You accidentally put the
space heater too close, Jake.

18:29.543 --> 18:31.197
That's what the jury
needs to hear. [coughs]

18:31.240 --> 18:33.677
[coughs]Ooh, this'll put it out.

18:33.721 --> 18:34.722
No, that's not water.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.293
[screaming]

18:42.686 --> 18:44.253
Look at that coward
running away.

18:44.297 --> 18:48.649
Aah!

18:49.911 --> 18:51.695
COOPER:
Nice one, Jake.

18:51.739 --> 18:54.307
Good thing I fixed
that hose earlier.

18:54.350 --> 18:57.440
Has anybody tried these
lettuce wraps? They're amazing.

18:58.615 --> 19:00.095
Well, better go.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.141
Got my first date
since the big divorce.

19:02.184 --> 19:03.577
Real special lady, too.

19:03.620 --> 19:05.492
I'm taking her up
in a hot air balloon.

19:07.189 --> 19:09.670
Yeah, for the next four hours,
it'll just be me, her

19:09.713 --> 19:12.629
and the sweet silence
of life in the clouds.

19:12.673 --> 19:14.675
Mmm.

19:24.424 --> 19:25.947
Oh, God.

19:25.990 --> 19:29.385
Oh, babe, you are sick.

19:29.429 --> 19:31.605
Why don't you come
lay down on the couch?

19:31.648 --> 19:33.781
All the embers are out.

19:33.824 --> 19:37.437
No, no, no, I-I-I said
I was gonna take care of you

19:37.480 --> 19:39.874
and that is exactly what
I'm gonna d... [gags]

19:39.917 --> 19:42.616
Claire, hold my hair back.
Claire. [gags]

19:42.659 --> 19:44.531
Babe, come on.

19:44.574 --> 19:46.010
So you made one little mistake.

19:46.054 --> 19:47.229
It's okay to admit it.

19:47.273 --> 19:49.057
No, it isn't.

19:49.100 --> 19:51.842
If I can't even take care
of my wife when she's sick,

19:51.886 --> 19:54.541
how am I ever gonna be able
to take care of a kid?

19:54.584 --> 19:56.456
[laughing]:
Don't worry.

19:56.499 --> 19:58.632
After what you did today,

19:58.675 --> 20:01.112
no one's gonna trust you
with their kid.

20:02.331 --> 20:04.464
[laughs]
No, seriously.

20:04.507 --> 20:06.161
Honey, you put
your own needs aside

20:06.205 --> 20:08.119
to take care
of everyone else.

20:08.163 --> 20:09.991
And if that's not proof
you're gonna be a great parent,

20:10.034 --> 20:11.601
I don't know what is.

20:11.645 --> 20:15.083
I guess that's true.
It is.

20:15.126 --> 20:18.434
And even if you did
poison everyone else,

20:18.478 --> 20:20.654
I'm actually starting
to feel better,

20:20.697 --> 20:23.961
so technically,
you did take care of me.

20:24.005 --> 20:26.312
Yeah, you're right.[chuckles]

20:26.355 --> 20:27.530
I'm the best husband ever.

20:27.574 --> 20:29.924
All right, so now that
you've proven that,

20:29.967 --> 20:32.274
can we still rely
on my parents to do some stuff?

20:32.318 --> 20:35.843
Oh, it'll probably be kind of
helpful when we have kids, huh?

20:35.886 --> 20:37.627
Yeah, yeah. We can get them
to do all the stuff

20:37.671 --> 20:39.238
that we don't want to do.

20:39.281 --> 20:42.284
You know, like-like assembling
strollers and changing diapers.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.329
Paying for college.

20:43.372 --> 20:45.200
They would be
so good at that.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.942
So good.
[laughs]

20:47.985 --> 20:50.031
Okay. Thank you again
for taking care of me.

20:50.074 --> 20:52.163
I love you.
I love you, too.

20:52.207 --> 20:53.774
Oh.
Mmm.

